page.title: 01FENDRAYTON AREA
page.content: To the west of the area you can see a part of{Fenstanton}which is mainly housing.The main village{Fendrayton, slightly smaller than{Fenstanton,}has things{Fenstanton}does not,like{green {houses,nurseries and farms.} Towards the west there is a{gravel {pit. {Fendrayton is fenland}as well as {Fenstanton}and there are many{drains. There are quite a few{roads}which are{straight and bumpy. Swavesey}is on the east of the map. There are{few trees.}The land is {mainly farmland; drained fen.} Both{Fenstanton}and{Fendrayton}have schools.{Fendrayton}has few facilities _a post office,a pub, a church and 2 shops. Towards the north there is a{disused {railway line}and also{disused gravel {pits.
